@page "/enigma-multiplayer"

<SeoHead Title="Enigma Multiplayer | Co-op Maze Sessions and Shared Puzzle Runs"
         Description="Learn how Enigma co-op works, from invites and ready checks to synchronized room state, shared puzzle progress, and team completion."
         OpenGraphType="article"
         SchemaType="Article"
         Keywords="Enigma multiplayer, co-op maze game, shared puzzle runs, cooperative puzzle maze" />

<div class="content seo-page-shell">
    <section class="panel seo-page-hero">
        <span class="profile-kicker">Co-op</span>
        <h1>Enigma Multiplayer</h1>
        <p>Enigma multiplayer is built for two-player cooperative runs with shared room progression, synchronized puzzle state, and live session updates.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Session Flow</h2>
        <h3>Create and Invite</h3>
        <p>The session owner starts a co-op lobby and invites a friend from their active friends list.</p>
        <h3>Join from Anywhere</h3>
        <p>Invites appear as live notifications and in the co-op lobby queue, so invited players can respond quickly without manual refresh.</p>
        <h3>Ready Check</h3>
        <p>Both players must be present and ready before entering the shared maze.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Shared Run Rules</h2>
        <h3>Synchronized Room State</h3>
        <p>Room transitions, puzzle completion, and major run events are synchronized at the session level.</p>
        <h3>Shared Objective Progress</h3>
        <p>Co-op puzzles and finish objectives are tracked for the team, not as separate solo attempts.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Completion and Failure</h2>
        <h3>Team Completion</h3>
        <p>A co-op run completes when both players satisfy the session finish conditions.</p>
        <h3>Session Abandonment</h3>
        <p>If a player leaves during an active co-op run, the session is marked abandoned and the run is recorded as a loss.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Live Multiplayer UX</h2>
        <h3>Status and Presence</h3>
        <p>Player online status, friend activity, and invite state are updated dynamically to reduce lobby friction.</p>
        <h3>Notification System</h3>
        <p>Invite arrivals, joins, and session state changes use the global app notification stream for fast feedback.</p>
    </section>
</div>
